  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6585 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-4623M) and positive gamma at 6605 (+1336M), dealers are currently in forced buying mode as we approach their short gamma squeeze zone. The breakout regime combined with the detected GEX surge suggests dealers are scrambling to hedge short gamma positions, creating amplified buying pressure that should drive price toward the 6605 resistance where they'll aggressively sell. Key battle zone is 6500-6605 corridor - break below 6500 triggers cascading dealer buying into the next negative wall at 6450, while sustained move above 6605 faces heavy dealer selling pressure.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile swings with upward bias until hitting strong resistance around 6605.",
